<meta content="TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript: Ann Morgan considered herself well read -- until she discovered the &quot;massive blindspot&quot; on her bookshelf. Amid a multitude of English and American authors, there were very few books from beyond the English-speaking world. So she set an ambitious goal: to read one book from every country in the world over the course of a year. Now she&#39;s urging other Anglophiles to read translated works so that publishers will work harder to bring foreign literary gems back to their shores. Explore interactive maps of her reading journey here: go.ted.com/readtheworld" name="description" />
